readability_reflection: I found string interpolation to be more readable as quotation marks can get lost in between the +`s.
comprehension_debugging: String interpolation made it easier to know where spaces should go which made it faster to understand.
preference_rationale: I would chose string interpolation based on the previously stated reasons.
learning_curve: I am more familiar with concatenation so at first this was easier to understand, especially with some of the more simple sentences. However, as sentences became longer and variables were introduces, I found string interpolation to be easier to read.
